# Refund Payment Service

This module handles refund requests for completed payment transactions.

<contract_rules>
R1 - Zero-amount refund rejection

For every refund request,
the system MUST reject requests where the refund amount is zero or negative
when the amount field is provided.

This rule is violated if a zero-amount refund is accepted and recorded.

R2 - Over-refund prevention

For every refund request,
the system MUST NOT allow a refund amount to exceed the original charge amount
when the original charge exists in the database.

This rule is violated if a refund greater than the charge is processed.

R3 - Provider call skipped for invalid requests

For every invalid refund request (zero, negative, or over-refund),
the system MUST NOT call the payment provider API
when the validation check has already failed.

R4 - Idempotency key on retry

For every refund retry,
the system MUST use the same idempotency key
when the original refund ID is provided in the request.

R5 - Audit log on completion

For every successful refund,
the system MUST write an audit log entry
when the payment provider confirms the refund.

R6 - Secret material isolation

The service MUST NOT log or return any payment provider credentials
when handling refund API responses.
</contract_rules>

<vocabulary>
refund amount: the monetary value to be returned to the customer, must be positive
original charge: the payment transaction that is being refunded
idempotency key: a client-supplied unique token ensuring duplicate requests are safe
payment provider: the external payment gateway (e.g. Stripe, Braintree)
</vocabulary>

<coverage>
R1: story__refund_invalid.md, test_R1_rejects_zero_refund
R2: story__refund_invalid.md
R3: test_R3_no_provider_call_invalid
R4: story__refund_idempotency.md
R6: WAIVED W1
</coverage>

<waivers>
W1:
  Rule: R6
  Approved by: Security team (2025-12-01)
  Rationale: Provider credentials are handled entirely by the provider SDK;
             this service never touches raw secrets. Verified 2025-12-01.
  Expires: 2026-12-01
</waivers>

<capabilities>
- The system MUST process refund requests within 5 seconds under normal load.
- The system SHOULD provide a human-readable error message for rejected refunds.
</capabilities>

<non_responsibilities>
- The service DOES NOT handle disputes or chargebacks.
- The service DOES NOT store payment card data.
</non_responsibilities>
